rows.label: qst200218_msg0001
rows.name:
So if we wait here, Harghal ought
to show up, right?

rows.label: qst200218_msg0003
rows.name:
That is the hope.
Let us have faith in our plan!

rows.label: qst200218_msg0004
rows.name: ...I don't see any girls showing up.

rows.label: qst200218_msg0005
rows.name: You don't think we have been tricked?

rows.label: qst200218_msg0006
rows.name: Hmmmm... I don't know about that.

rows.label: qst200218_msg0017
rows.name:
Maybe she's cautious enough
not to show herself unless she
absolutely has to.

rows.label: qst200218_msg0007
rows.name:
I guess we'd better try asking
an informant for more info.

rows.label: qst200218_msg0008
rows.name: To Teos Aure's black market it is, then.

rows.label: qst200218_msg0010
rows.name:
The black market... That would be a
place where villains do business, right?
Can I rain sweet justice upon them?

rows.label: qst200218_msg0011
rows.name:
You can not!
What are you, an idiot?!

rows.label: qst200218_msg0012
rows.name:
Listen, Glen, it may be called a
black market, but it's not actually
that bad of a place.

rows.label: qst200218_msg0013
rows.name:
If the black market disappeared from
Teos Aure, the people really would
starve to death.

rows.label: qst200218_msg0015
rows.name:
Really. There's plenty of upstanding
folk doing business there too. They just
don't have official permission, that's all.

rows.label: qst200218_msg0016
rows.name: A necessary evil for people to live...

rows.label: qst200218_msg0018
rows.name:
Guohhhhhh!
The notion pains me so!
